 using second-order Taylor expansion.
 The relationship between the minimum value of a convex function and the
 point near it can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
f(x+\Delta x)=f(x)+f'\Delta x+\Delta xH(x)\Delta x+O(\Delta x^{3})
\end{equation}

